    "content": "If you receive an error No route to host with any of the following steps, use the Troubleshoot Ansible steps ​\rRDP to OOB\rfrom Terminal in OOB cd /home/fortinet/automation/ansible/ubuntu ./create_tcgui.sh ../vars/all-hosts.yml \u003cPVE server name\u003e ubuntu_tcgui ./start_stop_remove_vm.sh ../vars/all-hosts.yml \u003cPVE server name\u003e ubuntu_tcgui started\r​\rContinuing from Terminal in OOB\rMake sure TCGUI VM has fully started (GUI is up and running) before exeucting the following. Suggest opening TCGUI’s console window on PVE to verify. ./configure_tcgui.sh ubuntu_tcgui ./wallpaper_update.sh ubuntu_tcgui ./start_stop_remove_vm.sh ../vars/all-hosts.yml \u003cPVE server name\u003e ubuntu_tcgui stopped ./start_stop_remove_vm.sh ../vars/all-hosts.yml \u003cPVE server name\u003e ubuntu_tcgui started",
    "description": "If you receive an error No route to host with any of the following steps, use the Troubleshoot Ansible steps ​\rRDP to OOB\rfrom Terminal in OOB cd /home/fortinet/automation/ansible/ubuntu ./create_tcgui.sh ../vars/all-hosts.yml \u003cPVE server name\u003e ubuntu_tcgui ./start_stop_remove_vm.sh ../vars/all-hosts.yml \u003cPVE server name\u003e ubuntu_tcgui started\r​\rContinuing from Terminal in OOB\rMake sure TCGUI VM has fully started (GUI is up and running) before exeucting the following. Suggest opening TCGUI’s console window on PVE to verify. ./configure_tcgui.sh ubuntu_tcgui ./wallpaper_update.sh ubuntu_tcgui ./start_stop_remove_vm.sh ../vars/all-hosts.yml \u003cPVE server name\u003e ubuntu_tcgui stopped ./start_stop_remove_vm.sh ../vars/all-hosts.yml \u003cPVE server name\u003e ubuntu_tcgui started",
